yn]]<sup>1</sup>\n|bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|[[Edward Villiers, 5th Earl of Clarendon|Villiers]]\n| colspan=\"4\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|[[James Gwynne-Holford|Gwynne-Holford]]\n| colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Cyril Flower, 1st Baron Battersea|Flower]]\n|-\n|[[Breconshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Breconshire]]\n| colspan=\"6\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Thomas Wood (1777-1860)|Wood]]\n| colspan=\"6\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Sir Joseph Bailey, 1st Baronet|Bailey]]\n| colspan=\"11\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|[[Godfrey Morgan, 1st Viscount Tredegar|G. Morgan]]\n| colspan=\"4\" bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|[[William Fuller-Maitland|Fuller-Maitland]]\n|}\n<sup>1</sup> original victor [[John Pratt, 3rd Marquess Camden|Pratt]] (Liberal) declared void on petition\n\n===1885 to 1918===\n{{legend2|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Liberal Party (UK)|Liberal]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Constituency\n!1885\n!1886\n!1892\n!''94''\n!1895\n!1900\n!1906\n!Jan 1910\n!Dec 1910\n|-\n|[[Montgomery (UK Parliament constituency)|Montgomery District]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Pryce Pryce-Jones|P. Pryce-Jones]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Frederick Hanbury-Tracy|Hanbury-Tracy]]\n| colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Pryce Pryce-Jones|P. Pryce-Jones]]\n| colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |E. Pryce-Jones\n| colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[John David Rees|Rees]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |E. Pryce-Jones\n|-\n|[[Montgomeryshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Montgomeryshire]]\n| colspan=\"3\" bg