|Livsey]]\n| colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Roger Williams (UK politician)|R. Williams]]\n| colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Christopher Davies (Conservative politician)|C. Davies]]\n|bgcolor={{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Jane Dodds|Dodds]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|[[Fay Jones (politician)|Jones]]\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Parliamentary constituencies in Wales]]\n\n== Notes and references ==\n;References\n{{reflist}}\n;Notes\n{{reflist|group=n}}\n\n{{UK constituencies}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Parliamentary Constituencies In Powys}}\n[[Category:Lists of United Kingdom Parliamentary constituencies in Wales|Powys]]\n[[Category:Powys|Parliamentary constituencies]]\n", "text_old": "'''Powys''' is divided into two constituencies of the [[House of Commons (UK)|House of Commons]] of the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom|UK Parliament]] ([[Palace of Westminster|Westminster]]), which are also used for elections to the [[National Assembly for Wales]].{{refn|group=n|[[County constituencies|county constituencies (CCs) for the purposes of type of returning officer and level of expenses]]; an esoteric and largely academic distinction is therefore sometimes made between borough and county constituencies}} The current boundaries have been effective since the [[2007 National Assembly for Wales election]] and the [[2010 United Kingdom general election|2010 UK general election]].<ref>[http://www.opsi.gov.uk/si/si2006/20061041.htm ''The Parliamentary Constituencies and Assembly Electoral Regions (Wales) Order 2006'', OPSI website]</ref>\n\n[[Powys]] is one of the eight [[Preserved counties of Wales|preserved counties]] of [[Wales]], and has the name and boundaries of one of the 22 [[Principal areas of Wales|principal areas]].\n\nFor Welsh Assembly elections, constituencies are grouped into [[Additional member system|additional member]] [[National Assembly for Wales constituencies and regions|electoral regions]], and changes to constituency boundaries mean, also, changes to regional boundaries.\n\n== Westminster boundaries ==\n\n=== From 2010 ===\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Brecon and Radnorshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Brecon and Radnorshire CC (Westminster)]] || rowspan=3| [[Image:PowysParliamentaryConstituencies2007.svg|left|132px|Parliamentary constituencies in Powys 2010]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Montgomeryshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Montgomeryshire CC (Westminster)]]\n|}\n\n{{legend2|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] \u2020|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrat]] \u00a4|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=1|Constituency\n!rowspan=1|Electorate\n!rowspan=1|Majority\n!colspan=2 class=unsortable|[[Member of Parliament]]\n!colspan=2 class=unsortable|Nearest opposition\n<!--!rowspan=1 class=unsortable|Electoral wards<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.opsi.gov.uk/si/si2007/uksi_20071681_en_4|title=The Parliamentary Constituencies (Wales) Order 2007|publisher=Crown copyright|work=[[Office of Public Sector Information]]|accessdate=7 November 2009|date=13 June 2007}}</ref><ref>[[Boundary Commissions (United Kingdom)|Boundary Commission for Wales]] pp. 1004\u20131007</ref> -->\n!rowspan=1 class=unsortable|Map reference above\n|-\n|Brecon and Radnorshire\n|55,490\n|7,131\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Fay Jones (politician)|Fay Jones]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Jane Dodds]] \u00a4\n|1\n|-\n|Montgomeryshire\n|48,997\n|12,138\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Craig Williams (politician)|Craig Williams]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Kishan Devani \u00a4\n|2\n|}\n\n=== 1997 to 2010 ===\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Brecon and Radnorshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Brecon and Radnorshire CC (Westminster)]] || rowspan=3| [[Image:PowysParliamentaryConstituenciesPre2007.png|left|Parliamentary constituencies in Powys pre-2010]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Montgomeryshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Montgomeryshire CC (Westminster)]]\n|-\n| 3. [[Clwyd South (UK Parliament constituency)|Clwyd South CC (Westminster)]] (part)\n|}\n\nThe Clwyd South constituency was also partly a [[List of Parliamentary constituencies in Clwyd|Clwyd constituency]].\n\n==Changes proposed for 2022==\n\nAs part of the [[Sixth Periodic Review of Westminster constituencies]] the Boundary Commission for Wales proposed changes to almost all the existing Welsh Westminster constituencies, giving their proposals official names in either English or Wales and offering an alternative in the other language.<ref>[http://bcomm-wales.gov.uk/?skip=1&lang=en Final Recommendations 2018] Boundary Commission for Wales]</ref>\n\n*[[Brecon, Radnor and Montgomery (UK Parliament constituency)|Brecon, Radnor and Montgomery]]\n*[[De Clwyd a Gogledd Maldwyn (UK Parliament constituency)|De Clwyd a Gogledd Maldwyn]]\n*[[Ceredigion a Gogledd Sir Benfro (UK Parliament constituency)|Ceredigon a Gogledd Sir Benfro]]\n\n== Assembly boundaries ==\n\n=== From 2007 ===\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Assembly region !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Brecon and Radnorshire (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Brecon and Radnorshire CC (Assembly)]] ||rowspan=2| [[Mid and West Wales (National Assembly for Wales electoral region)|Mid and West Wales]] || rowspan=3| [[Image:PowysParliamentaryConstituencies2007.svg|left|132px|Assembly constituencies in Powys 2007]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Montgomeryshire (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Montgomeryshire CC (Assembly)]]\n|}\n\nThe Mid and West Wales region also includes five [[List of Parliamentary constituencies in Dyfed|Dyfed constituencies]] and one [[list of Parliamentary constituencies in Gwynedd|Gwynedd constituency]].\n\n=== 1999 to 2007 ===\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Assembly region !! bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"| Constituency boundaries\n|-\n| 1. [[Brecon and Radnorshire (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Brecon and Radnorshire CC (Assembly)]] ||rowspan=2| [[Mid and West Wales (National Assembly for Wales electoral region)|Mid and West Wales]] || rowspan=3| [[Image:PowysParliamentaryConstituenciesPre2007.png|left|Assembly constituencies in Powys pre-2007]]\n|-\n| 2. [[Montgomeryshire (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Montgomeryshire CC (Assembly)]]\n|-\n| 3. [[Clwyd South (National Assembly for Wales constituency)|Clwyd South CC (Assembly)]] (part)\n| [[North Wales (National Assembly for Wales electoral region)|North Wales]]\n|}\n\n==Results==\n\n===Westminster elections===\n\n{|\n|-\n! 2005\n! 2010\n! 2015\n! 2017\n|-\n| [[File:UK general election 2005 (Powys).png|Results of the UK general election 2005 for Powys]]\n| [[File:National Assembly for Wales election 2011 (Powys).png|132px|Results of the UK general election 2010 for Powys]]\n| [[File:UK general election 2015 (Powys).png|132px|Results of the UK general election 2015 for Powys]]\n| [[File:UK general election 2015 (Powys).png|132px|Results of the UK general election 2017 for Powys]]\n|}\n\n===Assembly elections===\n\n{|\n|-\n! 2007\n! 2011\n! 2016\n|-\n| [[File:National Assembly for Wales election 2007 (Powys).png|132px|Constituency results of the National Assembly for Wales election 2007 for Powys]]\n| [[File:National Assembly for Wales election 2011 (Powys).png|132px|Constituency results of the National Assembly for Wales el