n* Frisch, Morton J., ed. ''Selected Writings and Speeches of Alexander Hamilton.'' 1985.\n* Goebel, Julius, Jr., and Joseph H. Smith, eds. ''The Law Practice of Alexander Hamilton''. 5 vols. Columbia University Press, 1964\u201380. (comprehensive edition of Hamilton's legal papers)\n* Hamilton, Alexander. ''[[Report on Manufactures]]''. (economic program for the United States)\n* Hamilton, Alexander. ''[[Report on Public Credit]]''. (financial program for the United States)\n* Hamilton, Alexander; [[John Church Hamilton|Hamilton, John Church]]. ''The Works of Alexander Hamilton: Miscellanies, 1789\u20131795: France; Duties on imports; National bank; Manufactures; Revenue circulars; Reports on claims''. 1850. John F. Trow, printer. ([https://books.google.com/?id=75YoAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA149 free online e-book edition])\n* Hamilton, Alexander; [[James Madison|Madison, James]]; [[John Jay|Jay, John]]. ''[[The Federalist Papers]]''. (published under the shared pseudonym \"Publius\")\n* {{cite book |editor-last=Lodge |editor-first=Henry Cabot |title=The Works of Alexander Hamilton |volume=10 vols. |year=1904 |url=https://archive.org/details/worksalexanderh10hamigoog |type=full text online at Internet Archive |publisher=New York, London, G.P. Putnam's Sons }}\n* Morris, Richard, ed. ''Alexander Hamilton and the Founding of the Nation''. 1957. (excerpts from Hamilton's writings)\n* National Archives, [https://founders.archives.gov/about Founders Online] &ndash; searchable edition\n* Sylla, Richard and David J. Cowen, eds. ''Alexander Hamilton on Finance, Credit, and Debt'' (Columbia UP, 2018) 346 pp. (partly abridged version of key documents; [http://eh.net/?s=Sylla+Cowen%2C online review])\n* Syrett, Harold C., Jacob E. Cooke, and Barbara Chernow, eds. ''The Papers of Alexander Hamilton''. 27 vols. Columbia University Press, 1961\u201387. (Includes all letters and writings by Hamilton, and all important letters written to him; the definitive edition of Hamilton's works, intensively annotated)\n* Taylor, George Rogers, ed. ''Hamilton and the National Debt''. 1950. (excerpts from 1790s writings representing all sides)\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Sister project links |s=Author:Alexander Hamilton |wikt=Hamiltonism |v=no |b=Outline of U.S. History/The Formation of a National Government}}\n{{Library resources box |onlinebooks=yes |by=yes}}\n* [https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/amex/hamilton/ Alexander Hamilton on PBS' ''American Experience'']\n* [https://www.loc.gov/rr/program/bib/hamilton/ Alexander Hamilton: A Resource Guide] from the Library of Congress\n* [https://www.loc.gov/collections/alexander-hamilton-papers/about-this-collection/ Alexander Hamilton Papers] from the Library of Congress (newly available August 2017)\n* [https://founders.archives.gov/about/Hamilton The Papers of Alexander Hamilton], subset of [https://founders.archives.gov/ Founders Online] from the [[National Archives and Records Administration|National Archives]]\n* [http://www.alexanderhamiltonexhibition.org/  New-York Historical Society's Alexander Hamilton Exhibit]\n* {{gutenberg author |id=Hamilton+Alexander+(1757\u20131804) |name=Alexander Hamilton}}\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Alexander Hamilton}}\n* {{Librivox author |id=4266}}\n* [http://press-pubs.uchicago.edu/founders/documents/v1ch4s31.html Hamilton's Report on Manufactures (Columbia University Press)]\n* [http://bioguide.congress.gov/scripts/biodisplay.pl?index=H000101 Hamilton's Congressional biography]\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.ios.com/~alstone/forthebk.htm |title=Alexander Hamilton: Debate over a National Bank (February 23, 1791) |access-date=April 4, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20001110000000/http://www.ios.com/~alstone/forthebk.htm |archive-date=November 10, 2000 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}\n* [http://cdl.library.cornell.edu/cgi-bin/moa/moa-cgi?notisid=ABQ7578-0123-7 Alexander Hamilton] by [[Henry Cabot Lodge]]\n* [http://www.footnote.com/page/146 Alexander Hamilton's 